{
  "name": "Watch Function Test (v2)",
  "description": "Demonstrates wallet operations with watch functionality using the new TransactionBuilder.",
  "version": "2.0",
  "config": {
    "baseUrl": "http://localhost:3031"
  },
  "stanzas": [
    {
      "name": "introduction",
      "blocks": [
        {
          "type": "markdown",
          "content": [
            "# Watch Function Test",
            "",
            "This demo demonstrates wallet operations with automatic watch functionality:",
            "1. Setting up watchers to monitor balances and UTXOs",
            "2. Creating wallets and seeing watchers update",
            "3. Transferring funds and seeing watchers update again"
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "setup_watchers",
      "blocks": [
        {
          "type": "markdown",
          "content": [
            "## Setting Up Watchers",
            "",
            "First, let's set up watchers to monitor balances and UTXOs automatically. They will start in a pending state until the wallets are created."
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "code",
          "language": "javascript",
          "content": [
            "await watchBalance('jeff');",
            "await watchBalance('nancy');",
            "await watchWalletUtxos('jeff');",
            "console.log('Watchers set up successfully!');"
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "create_wallets",
      "blocks": [
        {
          "type": "markdown",
          "content": [
            "## Creating Wallets",
            "",
            "Now we'll create wallets for Jeff and Nancy. The watchers will automatically detect these new wallets and update their state."
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "code",
          "language": "javascript",
          "content": [
            "jeff = await createWallet('jeff', 50_000_000);",
            "console.log(`Jeff's wallet created with ${jeff.balance} lovelace`);",
            "nancy = await createWallet('nancy', 75_000_000);",
            "console.log(`Nancy's wallet created with ${nancy.balance} lovelace`);"
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "transfer_funds",
      "blocks": [
        {
          "type": "markdown",
          "content": [
            "## Transferring Funds",
            "",
            "Let's transfer 10 ADA from Jeff to Nancy. The watchers should update automatically to reflect the new balances."
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "code",
          "language": "javascript",
          "content": [
            "const nancyAddr = (await getWalletUtxos('nancy'))[0].address;",
            "const transferTx = await newTransaction('jeff')",
            "  .payToAddress(nancyAddr, 10_000_000)",
            "  .submit();",
            "",
            "console.log(`Transfer completed in transaction: ${transferTx.transactionId}`);",
            "console.log('Check the watcher panel for updated balances!');"
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "balance_verification",
      "blocks": [
        {
          "type": "markdown",
          "content": [
            "## Verifying Balances",
            "",
            "Let's manually verify the balances after the transfer to confirm the watcher output is correct."
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "code",
          "language": "javascript",
          "content": [
            "jeffBalance = await getBalance('jeff');",
            "nancyBalance = await getBalance('nancy');",
            "console.log(`Jeff's final balance: ${jeffBalance} lovelace`);",
            "console.log(`Nancy's final balance: ${nancyBalance} lovelace`);"
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}
